text: Agnes Margaretha Reuter (born 30 November 1928 â€“ 13 February 2012) was Dutch rower from Rotterdam, who competed in the single sculls. She was a member of rowing club . At the unofficial 1952 European Rowing Championships she won the single sculls event. She won the bronze medal in the single sculls at the 1954 European Rowing Championships. In 1955 she won her fifth national title.
